      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nausea and a little tremor are common side effects when you first start taking lithium, but you should absolutely be proactive about it. Since you're feeling these things, you need to immediately check your sodium levels and perhaps take a small dose of magnesium, which I recommend you do with a full glass of water. For the best next step, you should definitely reach out to your prescribing physician to discuss these symptoms and ensure your dosage is optimized.",
