      "content": "Dizziness and worsening tremors while on lithium are not just signs of dehydration; they are signs your levels might be off, which requires immediate attention. You should not wait until tomorrow to see if it goes away, especially with these symptoms. I strongly advise you to call your doctor's office right now, or if they are unavailable, go to an urgent care clinic for a blood test to check your lithium and electrolyte levels.",
